    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Front Cover, Cooling System, and Related
        Components - Removal - Vibration Damper
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s09.2.7" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Vibration Damper</title>
        <figure id="f3450009018" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM05/M05119.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Front Power Takeoff (PTO) pulley (if equipped)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 30 bolt (3)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front PTO pulley</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove three M10&#160;x&#160;30 bolts and front PTO pulley (if equipped).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450009019" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM05/M05120.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Vibration damper runout</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Vibration damper</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dial indicator</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>When prying crankshaft forward, use a block of wood between the prybar and front crankcase
                    cover.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Before removing vibration damper, inspect vibration damper for runout as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Attach
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_200.xml" xrefid="s09.t3">dial indicator with magnetic base</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s09.t3"/>
                    to front of crankcase. Position indicator point on vibration damper front surface.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Pry only in one direction to eliminate possible error induced by crankshaft end play.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Pry crankshaft forward and zero dial indicator. This becomes the baseline.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Turn crankshaft 90&#176;. Pry crankshaft forward and record reading.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Repeat at each surface every 90&#176;. If runout exceeds
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_198.xml" xrefid="s09.t1">specification</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s09.t1"/>, replace vibration damper.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450009020" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM05/M05121.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Vibration damper</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M12 x 59 bolt (4)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Vibration damper</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, support the vibration damper when removing bolts. The damper
                    can easily slide off the end of the crankshaft.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The vibration damper retaining bolts are not reusable.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard four M12&#160;x&#160;59 bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not immerse damper in petroleum based solvents. This can damage the
                    rubber damper element.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove vibration damper.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
